  "texts": [
    "• RST p wo: A probabilistic representation that omits labels, focusing instead on the probabilities to 2 https://github.com/seq-to-mind/DMRST_Parser 3 Appendix A details the grouping of discourse relations.",
    "express uncertainty in discourse connections.",
    "• RST p w: The most granular representation, retaining both types of discourse relations and their probabilistic weights for a full-fledged representation of discourse nuances.",
    "The inclusion of the relation label is contingent on whether we perform average-and-merge along the relation dimension (z-axis).",
    "Whether the approach is binary or based on uncertainty hinges on whether we replace the probability value with 1 or 0."
  ]
}